      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Implement asynchronous processing for high-throughput scenarios, and use caching for frequent queries to reduce compute overhead."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Optimizing Performance with BGE M3 FP16"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "FP16 precision cuts memory bandwidth requirements, enabling faster inference on modern GPUs. To optimize, enable mixed-precision training if fine-tuning, and monitor throughput using tools like NVIDIA Nsight. Benchmark your API with realistic workloads; typical latencies for BGE M3 FP16 range from 10-50ms per query on a V100 GPU. Adjust batch sizes dynamically based on traffic patterns to balance latency and resource utilization."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best Practices for Production Deployment"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Ensure robustness by implementing health checks and fallback mechanisms for model loading. Use vector databases like FAISS or Pinecone for efficient similarity search, and index embeddings with appropriate dimensions (1024 for BGE M3). Regularly update the model to incorporate improvements, and log key metrics such as embedding generation time and error rates. For security, validate input lengths and sanitize queries to prevent injection attacks."
          }
        ]
